## 5. Compatibility & Setup Guide

- Best Blade Matches
    - Outer Carbon: Great for players who want to add extra speed and crispness to the rubber's linear nature (e.g., Viscaria, TB ALC).
    - Inner Carbon: The optimal setup for balanced spin-attackers. It maximizes dwell time and looping safety (e.g., Innerforce ALC, Yasaka Ma Lin Carbon).
    - All-Wood: Excellent for developing players (5-ply) or semi-pros seeking maximum control and spin (7-ply like Clipper).
    - Mismatch Cases: Extremely hard, stiff, and fast blades (like Tamca 5000) might make the setup too rigid and unforgiving, shrinking the dwell time.

- Forehand vs. Backhand Recommendation
    - Forehand: Highly recommended. It supports full body mechanics, huge spin, and strong opening loops.
    - Backhand: Great for advanced players who have a strong, active backhand loop (Chiquita, off-the-bounce topspin). May be too hard/heavy for beginners to use on the backhand.

